 <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../539/38539.xml">
reality television</link> <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../796/5796.xml">
personality</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../916/48916.xml">
model</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../084/25084.xml">
guest speaker</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../914/914.xml">
author</link>, and occasional <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../753/753.xml">
actor</link>. Hill is best known as a cast member on the twelfth season of <it><link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../418/2690418.xml">
The Real World</link></it>, MTV's highly rated reality TV show.</p>

<sec>
<st>
Biography</st>

<ss1>
<st>
Early life</st>
<p>

Hill was born in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../124/151124.xml">
San Marcos, Texas</link>, but was raised predominantly in <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../998/1998.xml">
Austin</link></village>
, and considers Austin to be his hometown.  He has one brother and a sister.  Hill developed his sense of comedy in his later childhood and adolescence in response to the stress of constant relocation and domestic issues.  At the age of 16, Hill left home and became <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../410/5575410.xml">
emancipated</link>.  He went to the <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../031/32031.xml">
University of Texas at Austin</link></university>
 and majored in business.  To support himself through college, Hill worked as a shirtless bartender in a popular gay club, and modeled part-time.  Towards the latter days of his collegiate career, Hill married a woman who hasn't been identified publicly.</p>

</ss1>
<ss1>
<st>
<it>Real World: Las Vegas''</it></st>
<p>

Hill's marriage failed by the time he was selected by MTV to appear in the 12th season of the <it>Real World</it> reality series.  On the first episode, he met fellow castmates Brynn and <actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../153/9023153.xml">
Trishelle Cannatella</link></actor>
 for a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../265/223265.xml">
three way</link> makeout session in the hot tub.  Hill's dramatic relationship with Cannatella, along with his dynamic fight with Brynn, would help to garner MTV high ratings. The relationship would fizzle after a dramatic pregnancy scare.  </p>

</ss1>
<ss1>
<st>
Post <it>Real World''</it></st>
<p>

After <it>The Real World</it> ended, Hill appeared in several subsequent MTV shows, including various <it><series wordnetid="108457976" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../688/1475688.xml">
Real World/Road Rules Challenges</link></series>
</it>, , and was the host of <it><series wordnetid="108457976" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../377/4389377.xml">
Say What? Karaoke</link></series>
</it> for a season.  </p>

</ss1>
<ss1>
<st>
Personal life</st>
<p>

In 2007, Hill married designer Donna Katz. They welcomed their first child, son Riley James David, in April 2008.</p>

</ss1>
